''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"gg17\"/>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2018\n|[[Empire Award for Best Male Newcomer]]\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[MTV Movie Award for Best Actor in a Movie|MTV Movie Award for Best Performance in a Movie]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |title=MTV Movie & TV Awards: 'Black Panther,' 'Stranger Things' Top Nominations |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503235147/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |archivedate=May 3, 2018 |df=}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Ansel Elgort}}\n* {{SoundCloud}}\n* {{IMDb name|5052065|Ansel Elgort}}\n\n{{MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Elgort, Ansel}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American electronic musicians]]\n[[Category:Island Records artists]]\n[[Category:Jewish American male actors]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Norwegian descent]]\n[[Category:Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:American DJs]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n[[Category:Male actors of German descent]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Russian descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor, singer and DJ|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use American English|date = September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ansel Elgort\n| image              = Ansel Elgort (35875410045).jpg\n| caption            = Elgort at the premiere of ''[[Baby Driver]]'' in 2017\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1994|3|14|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[New York City]], U.S. <!--As per WP:LINKDIRECT and Template:infobox person, birthplace indicates city, state, then country. No need to spell out \"United States; 'U.S.' is fine.-->\n| education          = [[Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School]]\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actor\n* singer\n*DJ\n}}\n| partner            = Violetta Komyshan <!--GIRLFRIENDS, MARRIAGE AND PAST PARTNERS!-->\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n* [[Arthur Elgort]]\n* [[Grethe Barrett Holby]]\n}}\n| yearsactive        = 2012\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background          = solo_singer\n| alias               = Ans\u00f8lo\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[soul music|soul]]\n* [[Electronic music|electronic]]\n}}\n| instrument          = {{flatlist|\n* [[Singing|Vocals]]\n* [[Disc jockey|DJ]]\n}}\n| label               = {{flatlist|\n* [[Island Records|Island]]\n* [[Universal Music Group|Universal]] (2015\u2013present)\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Tom Staar]]\n* [[Too Many Zooz]]\n* [[Logic (musician)|Logic]]\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Ansel Elgort''' (born March 14, 1994)<ref name=twitref1>{{cite web |last=Elgort |first=Ansel |title=Ansel Elgort: \"I'm 19 today...that's my attempt at a birthday hat and blowing a noise maker...\" |publisher=Twitter |date=March 14, 2013 |url=https://www.twitter.com/AnselElgort/status/312203341721653248?p=v |accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref><ref name=chic1>{{cite news |last=Markey |first=Judy |title=This Picture Is Worth A Thousand Puzzles|pages= |newspaper=[[Chicago Sun-Times]] |date=December 15, 1994 |url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=CSTB&p_theme=cstb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB421F8A8885CD5&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref><ref name=nyt1>{{cite news |last=Ward |first=Timothy Jack |title=Family Albums: A Pro's Take (With Tips) |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=August 14, 1997 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/14/garden/family-albums-a-pro-s-take-with-tips.html |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113044433/http://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/14/garden/family-albums-a-pro-s-take-with-tips.html |archivedate=November 13, 2013 |df= }}</ref> is an American actor, singer, dancer, and DJ (under the name '''Ans\u00f8lo''').<ref name=THR/><ref name=bb>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7832934/ansel-elgort-baby-driver-2017-cover-story |first=Rebecca |last=Milzoff |title=Ansel Elgort Breaks Out With 'Baby Driver' and a Frank Oce@n-Approved Singing Career: 'I'm Hopefully Going to Pull It All Off' |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=June 15, 2017 |accessdate=July 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616035559/http://www.billbored.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7832934/ansel-elgort-baby-driver-2017-cover-story |archivedate=June 16, 2017 |df= }}</ref> Born to photographer [[Arthur Elgort]] and stage producer [[Grethe Barrett Holby]], he began his acting career with a supporting role in the horror film ''[[Carrie (2013 film)|Carrie]]'' (2013).\n\nElgort gained wider recognition for starring as a teenage cancer patient in the romantic drama ''[[The Fault in Our Stars (film)|The Fault in Our Stars]]'' (2014) and for his role in ''[[The Divergent Series]]'' franchise. In 2017, he played the title character in [[Edgar Wright]]'s action thriller ''[[Baby Driver]]'', for which he received a [[Golden Globe Award]] nomination for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Best Actor in a Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy]]. As a singer, he has released the singles \"Thief\" (2017) and \"Supernova\" (2018).\n\n==Early life==\nElgort was born in [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]].<ref name=interviewmag1>{{cite magazine |last=Cole |first=Rachel T. |title=Film: Ansel Elgort |magazine=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]] |date=March 18, 2013 |url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/ansel-elgort |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130609091446/http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/ansel-elgort |archivedate=June 9, 2013 |df= }}</ref> His parents are [[Arthur Elgort]], a fashion photographer who has worked extensively for ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' for over 30 years,<ref>{{cite web |title=Look Back at Arthur Elgort's Most Stunning Fashion Photos |url=https://www.thecut.com/2015/01/revisit-arthur-elgorts-iconic-fashion-photos.html |first=Erica |last=Schwiegershausen |date=January 15, 2015 |publisher=New York Magazine's The Cut}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |title=Photographer Arthur Elgort To Be Given the CFDA Board of Directors Award Tonight |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/photographer-arthur-elgort-to-be-given-the-cfda-board-of-directors-award |first=Mark |last=Holgate |date=June 6, 2011 |magazine=Vogue Magazine}}</ref> and [[Grethe Barrett Holby]], an opera director.<ref name=vog1>{{cite magazine |last=Schillinger |first=Liesl |title=Ansel Elgort Goes from High School to Off Broadway in Regrets |magazine=Vogue |date=March 28, 2012 |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/breaking-out-ansel-elgort-stars-in-regrets-off-broadway |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520213353/http://www.vogue.com/culture/article/breaking-out-ansel-elgort-stars-in-regrets-off-broadway/ |archivedate=May 20, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/at-home-with-the-elgort-family-1427378597.html|title=At Home With the Elgort Family|work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|date=September 4, 2014|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref><ref name=nytob2>{{cite news |title=Paid Notice: Deaths; HOLBY, AASE GRETHE |newspaper=The New York Times |date=February 1, 2012 |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E03E7D8133AF932A35751C0A9649D8B63 |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923072333/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E03E7D8133AF932A35751C0A9649D8B63 |archivedate=September 23, 2013 |df= }}</ref> Elgort's father is of [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian Jewish]] descent,<ref>{{cite magazine |title=The Remarkable Jewish Background of 'Baby Driver' Star Ansel Elgort |url=http://www.tabletmag.com/scroll/239789/the-remarkable-jewish-background-of-baby-driver-star-ansel-elgort |first=Jonathan |last=Zalman |date=July 3, 2017 |magazine=Tablet Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ansel Elgort's Star Rises With 'Divergent' Movie |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/transcript/transcript.php?storyId=291961138 |first=Robin |last=Young |date=March 20, 2014 |work=[[NPR]]}}</ref> and his mother is of [[Norwegian American|Norwegian]], [[English American|English]] and [[German American|German]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ansel Elgort: there's no fault with this star|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/film/ansel-elgort-there-s-no-fault-with-this-star-1.2017744|first=Donald|last=Clarke|date=November 28, 2014|work=[[The Irish Times]]|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.instyle.com/news/ansel-elgorts-adorable-holiday-plans|title=Ansel Elgort's Adorable Holiday Plans Will Make You Want to Join His Family|last=Stern|first=Claire|date=November 18, 2015|work=[[InStyle]]|accessdate=May 6, 2018|quote=\"We have Norwegian roots, so we like to acknowledge that,\"}}</ref><ref name=divref1>{{cite web |date=February 24, 2014 |url=http://www.divergentlife.com/2014/02/new-ansel-elgort-live-stream-q-200k.html |title=Ansel Elgort's Live Stream |work=Divergent Society.net |quote=Quote stated at 22:05 in the interview.}}</ref>\n\nElgort's Norwegian maternal grandmother, Aase-Grethe,<ref>{{cite web|first=Alexandra|last=Macon|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/sophie-ansel-arthur-elgort-eric-von-stroh-wedding-southampton|title=Sophie Elgort and Eric Von Stroh's Wedding in Southampton|work=Vogue magazine|date=October 29, 2014|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref> was in the [[Norwegian resistance movement|Norwegian resistance]] during [[World War II]] and saved Norwegian Jewish children by moving them into neutral [[Sweden during World War II|Sweden]]; because of these activities, she was imprisoned in a [[Internment|concentration camp]].<ref name=nytob2/><ref name=divref2>{{cite web |date=February 24, 2014 |url=http://www.divergentlife.com/2014/02/new-ansel-elgort-live-stream-q-200k.html |title=Ansel Elgort's Live Stream |work=Divergent Society.net |quote=Quote stated at 16:40 in the interview. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227150346/http://divergentsociety.net/divergentmovie/ansel-elgorts-live-stream/ |archivedate=February 27, 2014 |df= }}</ref> Elgort is named after photographer [[Ansel Adams]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Millennial Man- Ansel Elgort |url=http://www.townandcountrymag.com/leisure/arts-and-culture/news/a2660/ansel-elgort/ |first=Carl |last=Swanson |date=January 6, 2015 |publisher=Town & Country}}</ref>\n\nThe third of three children, he has two older siblings: sister Sophie Elgort (born 1986), a fashion photographer,<ref name=vmagref1>{{cite magazine |last=Lamphier |first=Jason |title=Teenage Daydream |pages= |magazine=[[V (American magazine)|V]] |date=2013 |url=http://www.vmagazine.com/site/content/814/teenage-daydream |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130825090245/http://www.vmagazine.com/site/content/814/teenage-daydream |archivedate=August 25, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |title=Ansel Elgort's Big Sis Is Launching a Lifestyle Website |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/ansel-elgorts-sister-sophie-launching-798829 |first=Kathryn |last=Romeyn |date=May 29, 2015 |magazine=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> and brother Warren Elgort (born 1989), a cinematographer.<ref>{{cite web|first=Zachary|last=Weiss|url=http://observer.com/2016/07/21-young-new-york-socialites-you-should-know/|title=21 Young New York Socialites You Should Know|work=[[New York Observer]]|date=July 26, 2016|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref> At age nine, his mother took him to try out for [[School of American Ballet]].<ref name=vog1 /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/movies/how-ansel-elgort-went-from-brother-to-lover-with-shailene-woodley-in-the-fault-in-our-stars-20140602-zrssf.html|title=How Ansel Elgort went from brother to lover with Shailene Woodley in The Fault in Our Stars|last=Cooney Carrillo|first=Jenny|date=May 30, 2014|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|publisher=|access-date=May 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/divergent-fault-stars-actor-ansel-687196|title=Next Big Thing: 'Divergent,' 'Fault in Our Stars' Actor Ansel Elgort (Video)|last=Ford|first=Rebecca|date=March 20, 2014|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=|access-date=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Elgort went on to study there for five years.<ref>{{cite web |title=New York city ballet gala|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/05/new-york-city-ballet-gala-ansel-elgort|date=May 4, 2018 |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nElgort attended [[The Professional Performing Arts School]], [[Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School]] and [[Stagedoor Manor]] summer camp.<ref name=\"interviewmag1\"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Ansel Elgort kicks acting career into high gear with 'Baby Driver' |url=http://torontosun.com/2017/06/23/ansel-elgort-kicks-acting-career-into-high-gear-with-baby-driver/wcm/01837a97-1cde-481f-9d23-7b3e7a10e00b |first=Liz |last=Braun |date=June 23, 2017 |work=[[Toronto Sun]]|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Audition Choice That Booked Ansel Elgort 'Baby Driver' |url=https://www.backstage.com/interview/audition-choice-booked-ansel-elgort-baby-driver/ |first=Benjamin|last=Lindsay|date=June 21, 2017|work=[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage]]|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref> Elgort started taking acting classes at age 12 and at LaGuardia, where he performed in a rendition of ''[[Hairspray (musical)|Hairspray]]'' with schoolmate [[Kyle Jean-Baptiste]] and starred in the school's productions of ''[[Guys and Dolls]]''.<ref name=vog1 /><ref name=kylejeanbaptiste>{{cite magazine |title=Kyle Jean-Baptiste Dead: Les Miserables Broadway Actor Dies at 21 |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/kyle-jean-baptiste-dead-les-miserables-broadway-actor-dies-at-21-2015298 |first=Stephanie |last=Webber |accessdate=August 29, 2015 |magazine=[[Us Weekly]] |date=August 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Acting===\nElgort's first professional acting appearance was a few months before graduating high school, just days after his 18th birthday, when he premiered a lead role in an [[Off-Broadway]] production of ''Regrets'' in March 2012.<ref name=vog1 /> His film debut was in the 2013 remake of ''[[Carrie (2013 film)|Carrie]]'', in the key secondary role of the lead character's prom date. His first highly publicized role was in ''[[Divergent (film)|Divergent]]'' (2014) as Caleb Prior, the brother of the lead character.\n\nImmediately after the filming of ''Divergent'' was completed, it was announced that Elgort would play Augustus Waters in the film adaptation of [[John Green (author)|John Green's]] [[The Fault in Our Stars|novel]] ''[[The Fault in Our Stars (film)|The Fault in Our Stars]]'' opposite Woodley, who would play Hazel Grace Lancaster.<ref name=ew1>{{cite magazine |last=Vilkomerson |first=Sara |title=Ansel Elgort offered lead in 'The Fault in Our Stars' opposite Shailene Woodley |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |date=May 10, 2013 |url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/05/10/ansel-elgort-gus-fault-in-our-stars |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603122028/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/05/10/ansel-elgort-gus-fault-in-our-stars/ |archivedate=June 3, 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film followed the story of Hazel, a teenage cancer patient, who is forced by her parents to attend a support group, where she subsequently meets and falls in love with Waters, an ex-basketball player. The film, directed by [[Josh Boone (director)|Josh Boone]], was released on June 6, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldberg |first=Matt |title=First Clip from \"The Fault In Our Stars\" starring Shailene Woodley and Ansel Elgort |url=https://collider.com/the-fault-in-our-stars-clip/ |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=April 14, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418233858/http://collider.com/the-fault-in-our-stars-clip/ |archivedate=April 18, 2014 |df= }}</ref> Elgort next co-starred in the dramatic film ''[[Men, Women & Children (film)|Men, Women & Children]]'', directed by [[Jason Reitman]] and released in October 2014.<ref name=HR1>{{cite news |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |title=Jason Reitman's 'Men, Women & Children' Adds Emma Thompson, Judy Greer, Dean Norris |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jason-reitmans-men-women-children-665958 |accessdate=December 18, 2013 |newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter |date=December 16, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218021436/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jason-reitmans-men-women-children-665958 |archivedate=December 18, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n[[File:Ansel Elgort 2014 Divergent Premiere (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Elgort at the premiere of ''Divergent'', 2014]]\nIn 2014, Elgort was named one of the best actors under 20 years of age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Staff |first1=The Playlist |title=On The Rise: 20 Actors To Watch That Are Under 20 |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2014/09/on-the-rise-20-actors-to-watch-that-are-under-20-272876/ |website=Indiewire |accessdate=February 16, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170217143828/http://www.indiewire.com/2014/09/on-the-rise-20-actors-to-watch-that-are-under-20-272876/ |archivedate=February 17, 2017 |df= }}</ref> Elgort reunited with [[Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz]] to present the award for Best Visual Effects at the 2015 [[Oscars]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Giardina |first=Carolyn |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-2015-best-visual-effects-773989 |title=Oscars 2015: Best Visual Effects: Interstellar Wins Award |newspaper=Hollywood Reporter |date=February 22, 2015 |accessdate=October 12, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151009145043/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-2015-best-visual-effects-773989 |archivedate=October 9, 2015 |df= }}</ref> He also reprised his role, Caleb Prior, in ''[[The Divergent Series: Insurgent]]'', the second film of the book series ''Divergent'', which was released March 20, 2015, and in the third film, ''[[The Divergent Series: Allegiant]]'', which was released on March 18, 2016.\n\nIn 2016, Elgort was on a shortlist of actors for the role of [[Han Solo]] in ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''. After [[Alden Ehrenreich]] was cast in May 2016, Elgort expressed some relief, saying that if he had been cast, he would have had to change his DJ name, Ans\u00f8lo.<ref>{{cite news |title=Here's The One Upside To Not Getting The New Han Solo Role |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/ansel-elgort-han-solo_us_57960a8ee4b02d5d5ed219cf |first=Todd |last=Van Luling |date=July 25, 2016 |work=Huffington Post}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Elgort played the title role in the action film ''[[Baby Driver]]'', directed by [[Edgar Wright]], and also starring [[Lily James]] and [[Kevin Spacey]]. Elgort's audition in 2014 required him to [[lip sync]] and dance to the song of his choosing.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Milzoff|first1=Rebecca|title=Ansel Elgort Breaks Out With 'Baby Driver' and a Frank Ocean-Approved Singing Career: 'I'm Hopefully Going to Pull It All Off'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7832934/ansel-elgort-baby-driver-2017-cover-story|website=Billboard|accessdate=December 18, 2017|date=June 15, 2017}}</ref> The film received positive reviews and performed well at the box office. He received a [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy]] nomination for it.<ref name=\"gg17\">{{cite news|author1=Merry, Stephanie|first=Yahr, Emily|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/12/11/golden-globes-nominations-2018-complete-coverage/ |title=Golden Globes nominations 2018: Complete list of nominations |date=December 11, 2017 |work=The Washington Post |accessdate=December 11, 2017 }}</ref> Also that year, Elgort played Addison Schacht in the drama thriller film ''[[November Criminals (film)|November Criminals]]'', an adaptation of the novel of [[The November Criminals|the same name]], starring again with Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstshowing.net/2015/ansel-elgort-to-join-november-criminals-with-chloe-grace-moretz/ |title=Ansel Elgort to Join 'November Criminals' with Chloe Grace Moretz |website=FirstShowing.net |date=August 1, 2015 |accessdate=October 12, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924050902/http://www.firstshowing.net/2015/ansel-elgort-to-join-november-criminals-with-chloe-grace-moretz/ |archivedate=September 24, 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nElgort stars in the film ''[[Billionaire Boys Club (2018 film)|Billionaire Boys Club]]'', opposite [[Kevin Spacey]], [[Cary Elwes]], [[Emma Roberts]] and [[Taron Egerton]] and directed by [[James Cox (director)|James Cox]]. Due to claims of sexual harassment against Spacey, the future of the film was uncertain and no release date was set.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/these-upcoming-kevin-spacey-movies-shows-may-be-in-trouble-now.html/?a=viewall|title=These Upcoming Kevin Spacey Projects May Be in Trouble Now|date=2017-12-01|work=The Cheat Sheet|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en-US}}</ref> The film was initially released through [[video on demand]] on July 17, 2018, prior to a [[limited release]] in theaters on August 17, 2018, by [[Vertical Entertainment]].<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kevin-spacey-movie-billionaire-boys-club-hit-theaters-1121334 Kevin Spacey Film 'Billionaire Boys Club' to Hit Select Theaters in August]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/kevin-spaceys-billionaire-boys-club-to-hit-theaters-in-august/|title=Return From Exile: Kevin Spacey's 'Billionaire Boys Club' to Hit Theaters in August (Exclusive)|website=[[The Wrap]]|first=Matt|last=Donelly|date=June 18, 2018|accessdate=June 18, 2018}}</ref> Elgort played the lead role in the 2019 release ''[[The Goldfinch (film)|The Goldfinch]]'', an adaptation of [[Donna Tartt]]'s novel.\n\n====Upcoming films====\nOn June 27, 2017, it was announced that Elgort would portray future [[President of the United States|President]] [[John F. Kennedy]] during his time in the [[United States Navy]] in the film ''Mayday 109''.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/06/27/ansel-elgort-young-jfk-mayday-109/ |title=Ansel Elgort cast as young JFK in Mayday 109 |last=Gettell |first=Oliver |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Time Inc.]] |location=United States |date=June 27, 2017 |accessdate=June 27, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628013442/http://ew.com/movies/2017/06/27/ansel-elgort-young-jfk-mayday-109/ |archivedate=June 28, 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\nOn February 9, 2018, it was reported that Elgort would costar alongside [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] and [[Zendaya]] in [[crime thriller]] ''Finest Kind'', in which two brothers, portrayed by Elgort and Gyllenhaal, \"strike a dangerous deal with a crime syndicate that draws them into the Boston underworld\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/jake-gyllenhaal-ansel-elgort-zendaya-finest-kind-movie-1202283940/|title=Jake Gyllenhaal, Ansel Elgort & Zendaya To Topline  Crime Thriller 'Finest Kind'|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=February 10, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn February 28, 2018, it was revealed that Elgort would star as [[Hans Christian Andersen]] in an untitled original [[musical film]] with music composed by [[Stephen Schwartz (composer)|Stephen Schwartz]] and script provided by [[David Magee]]. The film would find Elgort as Hans, \"a young man who trapped in a world of his own imagination. And as Hans searches for a way back to reality, he comes face-to-face with characters from his own fairy tales, nearly all of whom try to trap him in their world forever\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/ansel-elgort-hans-christian-andersen-musical-wicked-stephen-schwartz-craig-zadan-neil-meron-fox-2000-david-magee-1202305862/|title=Fox 2000 Wins Hans Christian Andersen Musical By 'Wicked's Stephen Schwartz, David Magee, Zadan & Meron; 'Baby Driver' Ansel Elgort Circling|first=Mike Fleming|last=Jr|date=February 28, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=May 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn October 1, 2018, it was reported that Elgort had been cast in the lead role of Tony in director [[Steven Spielberg]]'s adaptation of ''[[West Side Story]]''. Filming commenced at the end of September 2019.<ref>[https://variety.com/2018/film/news/ansel-elgort-west-side-story-steven-spielberg-1202964116/#article-comments Ansel Elgort to Star in Steven Spielberg's 'West Side Story']</ref>\n\nIn December 2018, it was announced that Elgort would be starring as the title character in a film adaptation of \"The Great High School Impostor\". The film is based on the true story of Artur Samarin, a Ukrainian man who in 2012 overstayed his visa and then posed as an American high school student from the ages of 19\u201323 years old. The film will be made by Participant Media and scripted by Mike Makowsky.<ref>Gary, Collinson (December 21, 2018). [https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2018/12/ansel-elgort-is-the-great-high-school-imposter/ \"Ansel Elgort is the Great High School Impostor.\"] Retrieved April 9, 2019.</ref>\n\nIn June 2019, it was announced that Elgort would play the role of American journalist [[Jake Adelstein]] in a television adaptation of Adelstein's non-fiction memoir ''[[Tokyo Vice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Joe Otterson |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/ansel-elgort-tokyo-vice-warnermedia-streaming-service-1203235293 |title=Ansel Elgort to Star in Drama Series \u2018Tokyo Vice\u2019 for WarnerMedia \u2013 Variety |website=Variety.com |date=2019-06-06 |accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Nellie Andreeva |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warnermedia-streamer-orders-tokyo-vice-drama-series-ansel-elgort-endeavor-content-1202628306 |title=WarnerMedia Streamer Orders \u2018Tokyo Vice\u2019 Series Starring Ansel Elgort \u2013 Deadline |website=Deadline.com |date=2019-06-06 |accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref> The ten-part television series tells the story of an American journalist who embeds himself into the Tokyo Vice police squad to reveal corruption. The series will be written and executive produced by Tony Award-winning playwright [[J. T. Rogers]], with the pilot episode directed by [[Michael Mann]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Mike Fleming Jr |url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/michael-mann-direct-pilot-tokyo-vice-ansel-elgort-ken-watanabe-hbo-max-1202766347/ |title=Michael Mann Direct Ansel Elgort Ken Watanabe HBO Max Pilot Tokyo Vice \u2013 Deadline |website=Deadline.com |date=2019-10-22 |accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref> and subsequent episodes directed by [[Destin Daniel Cretton]] (''Short Term 12'').  Endeavor Content will serve as the studio and [[John Lesher (producer)|John Lesher]] and [[Emily Gerson Saines]] will serve as executive producers, alongside Elgort, Rogers, and Mann. Tokyo Vice will debut on [[WarnerMedia]]'s upcoming streaming platform [[HBO Max]].\n\nElgort is represented by [[Creative Artists Agency|CAA]] and Brookside Artist Management's Emily Gerson Saines.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fleming |first=Mike |url=https://deadline.com/2014/06/ansel-elgort-fault-in-our-stars-van-cliburn-movie-794404/ |title='Fault In Our Stars' Ansel Elgort To Play Van Cliburn In Biopic |website=Deadline |date=June 23, 2014 |accessdate=October 12, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019070354/http://deadline.com/2014/06/ansel-elgort-fault-in-our-stars-van-cliburn-movie-794404/ |archivedate=October 19, 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Music===\n[[File:Ansel Elgort at an Apple Store in 2014 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Elgort in 2014]]\nUnder the name Ansolo, Elgort created a [[SoundCloud]] account to publish electronic dance music, and he has remixed songs such as \"[[Born to Die (song)|Born to Die]]\" by [[Lana del Rey]]. In a livestream in February 2014, he said he had signed a record deal with Tom Staar's new label, Staar Traxx, and [[Steve Angello]]'s label, Size Records.{{citation needed |date=August 2014}}\n\nHis first record, ''Unite'', was released on April 21, 2014, on [[Beatport]], and May 5, 2014, on [[iTunes]].<ref name=THR>{{cite magazine |author1=Ashley Lee |title=Ansel Elgort to Release Electronic Dance Music Record 'Unite' in April (Audio) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/audio-ansel-elgort-electronic-dance-music-unite-690256 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 13, 2014 |date=March 21, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720043821/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/audio-ansel-elgort-electronic-dance-music-unite-690256 |archivedate=July 20, 2014 |df= }}</ref> His second record, ''Totem'', was released July 21, 2014, on Beatport and iTunes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crossmap.com/news/ansel-elgort-aka-ansolos-totem-enters-top-music-charts-video-talks-musical-career-in-intimate-interview-11434 |title=Ansel Elgort AKA Ansolo's 'Totem' Enters Top Music Charts [VIDEO] Talks Musical Career in Intimate Interview |first=Alma L. |last=Cruz |website=Crossmap |date=July 22, 2014 |accessdate=July 9, 2017}}</ref> His single \"To Life\", a [[Bar and Bat Mitzvah|Bar Mitzvah]]-themed song inflected with [[klezmer]] music, was released in September 2015.<ref name=bb/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2275615/ansel-elgort-ansolo-to-life/ |title=Here's 'To Life,' A Brand-Spanking-New Song From Ansolo (AKA Ansel Elgort) |work=MTV News |first=Patrick |last=Hosken |date=September 18, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409142031/http://www.mtv.com/news/2275615/ansel-elgort-ansolo-to-life/ |archivedate=April 9, 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n\nElgort played at the [[Electric Zoo Festival]] main stage in 2014, the [[Ultra Music Festival]] main stage in March 2015, played in a red-light dance music event in [[Amsterdam]] in 2014, opened some [[The Chainsmokers]] shows, a [[Nervo (duo)|Nervo]] show and some others shows with his friends [[Nicky Romero]] and [[Martin Garrix]]. He played his first headline show on his 21st birthday on [[Pacha Group|Pacha NYC]].\n\nIn 2015, he signed a record deal with Island/Universal Records, releasing his first single on the label, \"Home Alone\", in July 8, 2016.\n \nOn February 3, 2017, he released a single called \"Thief\" under the name Ansel Elgort. The music video featured his girlfriend Violetta Komyshan, a [[ballet dancer]].\n\nHe was featured on rapper [[Logic (musician)|Logic]]'s third studio album, ''[[Everybody (Logic album)|Everybody]]'', released on May 5, 2017, on a song titled \"Killing Spree\".<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/05/stream-new-logic-album-everybody/ |title=Stream Logic's New Album 'Everybody' |magazine=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]] |accessdate=May 5, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505095636/http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/05/stream-new-logic-album-everybody/ |archivedate=May 5, 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2018, he released a single called \"Supernova\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q-oM2BQ8Jow|title=Ansel Elgort - Supernova|first=|last=AnselElgortVEVO|date=January 11, 2018|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2012, Elgort began dating his high school sweetheart, Violetta Komyshan, a ballet dancer. The couple broke up in August 2014 primarily due to the actor's burgeoning career and hectic schedule<ref>{{cite web |title=Ansel Elgort and High School Sweetheart Violetta Komyshan Break Up |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/573818/ansel-elgort-and-high-school-sweetheart-violetta-komyshan-break-up |work=eonline.com |first=Lily |last=Harrison |date=August 27, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150217192735/http://www.eonline.com/news/573818/ansel-elgort-and-high-school-sweetheart-violetta-komyshan-break-up |archivedate=February 17, 2015 |df= }}</ref> but reconciled in 2015.\n\nHe is a [[skateboarding|skateboarder]] and an avid sportsman, often seen playing pickup basketball. As a hobby, he also took to [[Figure painting (hobby)|miniature painting]], displaying some of his work.<ref name=bb/> He is an avid fan of the [[New York Mets]], [[New York Jets]], [[New York Knicks]] and [[New York Rangers]].\n\nHe currently resides in the Bedford Stuyvesant neighborhood in Brooklyn, NY.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Carrie (2013 film)|Carrie]]''\n| Tommy Ross\n| \n|-\n|  rowspan=3|2014\n| ''[[Divergent (film)|Divergent]]''\n| [[List of The Divergent trilogy characters#Caleb Prior|Caleb Prior]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Fault in Our Stars (film)|The Fault in Our Stars]]''\n| [[Augustus Waters]]\n| \n|-\n|''[[Men, Women & Chi